<main id="main" class="enterprise-page" data-enterprise-vision>
  <section class="enterprise-hero"><div class="shell"><p class="os-eyebrow">BUSINESS OF MEDICINE INTELLIGENCE</p><h1>Better physician decisions create better Business of Medicine intelligence.</h1><p>BOMSociety begins with the physician decision. Protected, anonymous outcomes improve the Decision Episode; only then can rigorously aggregated patterns inform an enterprise decision.</p><p class="enterprise-status">STATUS: IN DEVELOPMENT · Physicians remain free · Individual physician data is never sold.</p></div></section>
  <section class="enterprise-architecture"><div class="shell"><p class="os-eyebrow">THE OPERATING SYSTEM</p><h2>One direction. Physician value first.</h2><ol><li>Enterprise Intelligence Domain</li><li>Business of Medicine Domain</li><li>Decision Episode Library</li><li>30 sec / 2 min / 5 min</li><li>Physician Decisions</li><li>Anonymous Outcomes</li><li>Improved Guidance</li><li>Enterprise Intelligence</li></ol><p>No topic enters the library because it is popular. Enterprise intelligence requirements define domains; domains define Decision Episodes; Decision Episodes define the content.</p></div></section>
  <section class="enterprise-principles"><div class="shell"><p class="os-eyebrow">MISSION, PRIVACY &amp; METHOD</p><h2>Useful patterns begin with a protected Decision Episode.</h2><div class="enterprise-process"><article><b>01 · PHYSICIAN VALUE</b><h3>Start with the decision.</h3><p>Every episode has one mandatory primary intelligence-domain mapping and exists to improve a Business of Medicine decision.</p></article><article><b>02 · ANONYMOUS AGGREGATION</b><h3>Patterns only in groups.</h3><p>No identifiable physician profile, patient data, or raw document is a prerequisite for intelligence products.</p></article><article><b>03 · GOVERNED INFERENCE</b><h3>Evidence before a claim.</h3><p>Documented validation, minimum aggregation thresholds, and visible limitations come before a benchmark or recommendation.</p></article></div></div></section>
  <section class="enterprise-governance"><div class="shell enterprise-governance-grid"><div><p class="os-eyebrow">GOVERNANCE</p><h2>Trust is a product requirement.</h2><p>Physician benefit determines what is collected, how it is aggregated, and whether it is mature enough to share. No future product is available until these safeguards are satisfied.</p></div><ul><li>Aggregated intelligence only</li><li>No individual physician data sales</li><li>No patient data or raw contract documents</li><li>Transparent methodology and limitations</li><li>Minimum valid samples before any output</li><li>Physician Decision Episodes remain free</li></ul></div></section>
  <section class="enterprise-products"><div class="shell"><p class="os-eyebrow">INTELLIGENCE DOMAINS</p><h2>Ten permanent domains. Every one is in development.</h2><p class="enterprise-intro">Each domain names a real buyer, the business decision it can improve, the Decision Episodes that feed it, and the conditions required before any future product exists.</p><div class="enterprise-product-grid" data-enterprise-products>
    <details><summary><span>STATUS: IN DEVELOPMENT</span><h3>Compensation Intelligence™</h3><p>Clarifies compensation-formula decision patterns.</p></summary><div><p><b>Purpose:</b> improve compensation guidance and formula transparency.</p><p><b>Buyer / better decision:</b> health systems and large physician groups decide where formula design, communication, or reconciliation needs review.</p><p><b>Episodes:</b> Compensation (primary); Employment Contracts (secondary).</p><p><b>Validation / aggregation:</b> verified episode taxonomy; consented anonymous outcomes; minimum specialty, geography, and time-window thresholds.</p><p><b>Privacy:</b> no named physicians, employers, offers, or individual benchmarks.</p><p><b>Maturity:</b> episode foundation active. <b>Future product:</b> aggregate compensation-friction brief.</p></div></details>
    <details><summary><span>STATUS: IN DEVELOPMENT</span><h3>Contract Intelligence™</h3><p>Clarifies employment-contract decision patterns.</p></summary><div><p><b>Purpose:</b> improve guidance on terms, leverage, and restrictive covenants.</p><p><b>Buyer / better decision:</b> health systems, physician groups, and staffing organizations decide which contract terms require clearer, fairer communication.</p><p><b>Episodes:</b> Employment Contracts (primary); Compensation (secondary).</p><p><b>Validation / aggregation:</b> structured clause-topic taxonomy; anonymous action signals; minimum cohort and time-window thresholds.</p><p><b>Privacy:</b> no contracts, employer names, or individual negotiation histories.</p><p><b>Maturity:</b> episode in development. <b>Future product:</b> aggregate contract-question brief.</p></div></details>
    <details><summary><span>STATUS: IN DEVELOPMENT</span><h3>AI Adoption Intelligence™</h3><p>Clarifies practical AI adoption decisions.</p></summary><div><p><b>Purpose:</b> improve physician guidance on workflow value, oversight, data, and measurement.</p><p><b>Buyer / better decision:</b> health systems, AI vendors, and technology companies decide where implementation support and safeguards are needed.</p><p><b>Episodes:</b> Artificial Intelligence in Practice (primary); Technology Adoption (secondary).</p><p><b>Validation / aggregation:</b> workflow-use taxonomy; anonymous pilot reflections; minimum organization-type and time-window thresholds.</p><p><b>Privacy:</b> no patient data, tool-level user profiles, or identifiable performance data.</p><p><b>Maturity:</b> episode in development. <b>Future product:</b> aggregate adoption-readiness brief.</p></div></details>
    <details><summary><span>STATUS: IN DEVELOPMENT</span><h3>Revenue Cycle Intelligence™</h3><p>Clarifies coding and reimbursement decisions.</p></summary><div><p><b>Purpose:</b> improve physician guidance on documentation, coding, and reimbursement choices.</p><p><b>Buyer / better decision:</b> health systems, revenue-cycle companies, and physician groups decide where workflow education or escalation paths need improvement.</p><p><b>Episodes:</b> Revenue Cycle and Coding &amp; Compliance (primary).</p><p><b>Validation / aggregation:</b> validated topic taxonomy; anonymous action/outcome signals; minimum specialty and setting thresholds.</p><p><b>Privacy:</b> no patient data, claims, billing records, or individual performance reporting.</p><p><b>Maturity:</b> domain discovery. <b>Future product:</b> aggregate decision-friction report.</p></div></details>
    <details><summary><span>STATUS: IN DEVELOPMENT</span><h3>Practice Economics Intelligence™</h3><p>Clarifies the economics behind practice decisions.</p></summary><div><p><b>Purpose:</b> improve guidance on practice margins, capacity, and operational tradeoffs.</p><p><b>Buyer / better decision:</b> large physician groups, consulting firms, and PE-backed practice platforms decide where economic assumptions need clearer physician-facing explanation.</p><p><b>Episodes:</b> Practice Economics (primary); Practice Ownership and Productivity (secondary).</p><p><b>Validation / aggregation:</b> defined decision taxonomy; anonymous scenario/outcome patterns; minimum practice-type and time-window thresholds.</p><p><b>Privacy:</b> no practice financial statements, named practices, or individual earnings data.</p><p><b>Maturity:</b> domain discovery. <b>Future product:</b> aggregate practice-economics signal brief.</p></div></details>
    <details><summary><span>STATUS: IN DEVELOPMENT</span><h3>Practice Ownership Intelligence™</h3><p>Clarifies ownership and transaction decisions.</p></summary><div><p><b>Purpose:</b> improve guidance on ownership, buy-ins, affiliation, and control.</p><p><b>Buyer / better decision:</b> physician groups, PE-backed practice platforms, banks, and consulting firms decide what ownership questions need transparent decision support.</p><p><b>Episodes:</b> Practice Ownership (primary); Practice Economics (secondary).</p><p><b>Validation / aggregation:</b> ownership-pathway taxonomy; anonymous action signals; minimum ownership-model and regional thresholds.</p><p><b>Privacy:</b> no transaction documents, valuations, named buyers, or identifiable profiles.</p><p><b>Maturity:</b> episode in development. <b>Future product:</b> aggregate ownership-decision brief.</p></div></details>
    <details><summary><span>STATUS: IN DEVELOPMENT</span><h3>Leadership &amp; Operations Intelligence™</h3><p>Clarifies operational and leadership decisions.</p></summary><div><p><b>Purpose:</b> improve guidance on team, capacity, governance, and operations choices.</p><p><b>Buyer / better decision:</b> health systems, large physician groups, and specialty societies decide where operational support or governance conversations are most needed.</p><p><b>Episodes:</b> Leadership &amp; Operations (primary); Practice Economics (secondary).</p><p><b>Validation / aggregation:</b> decision-context taxonomy; anonymous completion and outcome signals; minimum role and setting thresholds.</p><p><b>Privacy:</b> no employee-performance profiles or identifiable team reporting.</p><p><b>Maturity:</b> episode in development. <b>Future product:</b> aggregate operations-decision brief.</p></div></details>
    <details><summary><span>STATUS: IN DEVELOPMENT</span><h3>Productivity Intelligence™</h3><p>Clarifies productivity and workload decisions.</p></summary><div><p><b>Purpose:</b> improve guidance on workload, attribution, and productivity tradeoffs.</p><p><b>Buyer / better decision:</b> health systems, physician groups, and staffing organizations decide where workload expectations and productivity rules need review.</p><p><b>Episodes:</b> Productivity (primary); Compensation and Leadership &amp; Operations (secondary).</p><p><b>Validation / aggregation:</b> workload taxonomy; anonymous decision/outcome signals; minimum specialty and employment-model thresholds.</p><p><b>Privacy:</b> no individual productivity scores, schedules, or employer comparisons.</p><p><b>Maturity:</b> domain discovery. <b>Future product:</b> aggregate workload-clarity brief.</p></div></details>
    <details><summary><span>STATUS: IN DEVELOPMENT</span><h3>Technology Adoption Intelligence™</h3><p>Clarifies non-AI technology adoption decisions.</p></summary><div><p><b>Purpose:</b> improve guidance on selecting, implementing, and evaluating practice technology.</p><p><b>Buyer / better decision:</b> technology companies, health systems, and medical schools decide where adoption support, training, or implementation design needs improvement.</p><p><b>Episodes:</b> Technology Adoption (primary); Artificial Intelligence in Practice (secondary).</p><p><b>Validation / aggregation:</b> technology-decision taxonomy; anonymous implementation reflections; minimum setting and time-window thresholds.</p><p><b>Privacy:</b> no vendor user tracking, patient data, or identifiable adoption profiles.</p><p><b>Maturity:</b> domain discovery. <b>Future product:</b> aggregate implementation-readiness brief.</p></div></details>
    <details><summary><span>STATUS: IN DEVELOPMENT</span><h3>Physician Wealth Intelligence™</h3><p>Clarifies physician financial decisions.</p></summary><div><p><b>Purpose:</b> improve guidance on wealth, insurance, investing, and retirement choices.</p><p><b>Buyer / better decision:</b> banks, insurers, medical schools, and specialty societies decide where physician financial decision support is most needed.</p><p><b>Episodes:</b> Physician Wealth (primary); Compensation (secondary).</p><p><b>Validation / aggregation:</b> financial-decision taxonomy; anonymous action signals; minimum career-stage and time-window thresholds.</p><p><b>Privacy:</b> no account data, balances, portfolios, insurance applications, or individual financial profiles.</p><p><b>Maturity:</b> episode in development. <b>Future product:</b> aggregate financial-decision needs brief.</p></div></details>
  </div></div></section>
  <section class="enterprise-methodology"><div class="shell"><p class="os-eyebrow">METHODOLOGY</p><h2>Evidence before inference.</h2><p>Future outputs will state the domain, buyer decision, source signals, validation method, aggregation threshold, privacy safeguards, and limitations. They will not claim to represent individual physicians or an unvalidated market.</p><a class="os-text-link" href="{{@site.url}}/methodology/">Explore the methodology <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></a></div></section>
  <section class="enterprise-pilots"><div class="shell"><p class="os-eyebrow">PILOT DISCUSSIONS</p><h2>Help test the standard before anything is sold.</h2><p>We are listening to organizations that want to pressure-test a specific buyer decision, governance standard, and physician benefit. These are pilot discussions—not product sales.</p><a class="os-button" href="{{@site.url}}/contact/">Start a pilot discussion <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></a></div></section>
